</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dounas, C. G." journalOrPublisher="University of Thessaloniki, Thessaloniki" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Study of the macrofaunal assemblages of Strymonikos Gulf" year="1986">Dounas (1986)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Arvanitidis, Christos" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, Thessaloniki" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Συστηματική και βιονομική μελέτη των μακροβενθικών πολυxαίτων (AnnelidaPolychaeta) του Βορείου Αιγαίου" year="1994">Arvanitidis (1994)</bibRefCitation>
. In the Mediterranean also known from France (
<bibRefCitation author="Fiege, Dieter" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="215 - 234" title="A partial review of the European Magelonidae (Annelida: Polychaeta): Magelonamirabilis redefined and M. johnstoni sp. nov. distinguished" volume="80" year="2000">Fiege et al. 2000b</bibRefCitation>
), Italy (
<bibRefCitation author="Castelli, A" journalOrPublisher="Biologia Marina Mediterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="323 - 373" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta" volume="15" year="2008">Castelli et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
), Turkey (
<bibRefCitation author="Cinar, Melih Ertan" journalOrPublisher="Turkish Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 31" title="Check-List of Annelida from the Coasts of Turkey" volume="38" year="2014">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Çınar">Cinar</normalizedToken>
et al. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
) and the Adriatic (
<bibRefCitation author="Mikac, Barbara" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 17" title="A sea of worms: polychaete checklist of the Adriatic Sea" volume="3943" year="2015">Mikac 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Probably underreported, since older records of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Magelonidae" genus="Magelona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magelona cincta" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cincta">Magelona cincta</taxonomicName>
Ehlers, 1908 may belong to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Magelonidae" genus="Magelona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magelona alleni" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="alleni">Magelona alleni</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson, D. P." journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="617 - 626" title="The polychaete Magelonaalleni n. sp. and a re-assessment of Magelonacincta Ehlers" volume="37" year="1958">Wilson 1958</bibRefCitation>
; see also notes under 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Magelonidae" genus="Magelona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Magelona cincta" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cincta">Magelona cincta</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
